    """     """
    return ingredient_mapping.get(drug_code, drug_code)  #

#       10  
top_10_drugs = df[""].value_counts().head(10).index
top_10_labels = [get_ingredient_name(code) for code in top_10_drugs]

#      
df_gender_drug_ratio = df[df[""].isin(top_10_drugs)].groupby(["", ""]).size().unstack().fillna(0)

#     
df_gender_drug_ratio = df_gender_drug_ratio.div(df_gender_drug_ratio.sum(axis=1), axis=0) * 100

#   
df_gender_drug_ratio.index = [get_ingredient_name(code) for code in df_gender_drug_ratio.index]

#   (1  , 2  )
df_gender_drug_ratio.columns = ["(%)", "(%)"]

# CSV  
df_gender_drug_ratio_csv = df_gender_drug_ratio.copy().reset_index()
df_gender_drug_ratio_csv.rename(columns={"index": ""}, inplace=True)
df_gender_drug_ratio_csv.to_csv(os.path.join(powerbi_data_DIR, "PowerBI_gender_top10_prescriptions.csv"), encoding="cp949", index=False)

#    
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 6))
df_gender_drug_ratio.plot(kind="barh", stacked=True, color=["blue", "pink"], ax=ax)

ax.set_title("  10    ")
ax.set_xlabel(" (%)")
ax.set_ylabel("")
ax.legend(title="", bbox_to_anchor=(1.05, 1), loc="upper left")

plt.grid(axis="x", linestyle="--", alpha=0.7)
plt.show()

df_region_ratio.columns = ["", "(%)"]

#       
df_pyramid = df.groupby(["", ""]).size().unstack().fillna(0)

#       
df_pyramid_ratio = df_pyramid.div(df_pyramid.sum().sum()) * 100  #     

#       
df_pyramid_ratio.columns = [age_mapping[i] for i in df_pyramid_ratio.columns]

# ( 1), ( 2)  
male_ratios = -df_pyramid_ratio.loc[1]  #   (    )
female_ratios = df_pyramid_ratio.loc[2]  #   (    )

# CSV  
df_pyramid_csv = pd.DataFrame({"": df_pyramid_ratio.columns, "(%)": -male_ratios, "(%)": female_ratios})
df_pyramid_csv.to_csv(os.path.join(powerbi_data_DIR, "PowerBI_gender_age_pyramid_ratio.csv"), encoding="cp949", index=False)

#   
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))

#  ()
ax.barh(df_pyramid_ratio.columns, male_ratios, color="blue", label="")

#  ()
ax.barh(df_pyramid_ratio.columns, female_ratios, color="pink", label="")

ax.set_title("     ")
ax.set_xlabel(" (%)")
ax.set_ylabel("")
ax.legend()

#  0    
max_ratio = max(abs(male_ratios.max()), female_ratios.max())
ax.set_xlim(-max_ratio * 1.1, max_ratio * 1.1)

plt.grid(axis="x", linestyle="--", alpha=0.7)
plt.show()

# Z-score  
def z_score_normalization(series):
    return (series - series.mean()) / series.std()

#   
antihistamines = {
    "130501ATB": "",
    "131801ATB": "",
    "347901ATB": ""
}

# /   
df_total_monthly = df.groupby("").size()

# /    
df_antihistamine_trend = pd.DataFrame()
for code, name in antihistamines.items():
    df_antihistamine_trend[name] = df[df[""] == code].groupby("").size()

# /       (%) 
df_antihistamine_trend = (df_antihistamine_trend.div(df_total_monthly, axis=0)) * 100

# Z-score  
df_normalized = df_antihistamine_trend.apply(z_score_normalization)

# CSV  
df_normalized_csv = df_normalized.copy()
df_normalized_csv.index = pd.to_datetime(df_normalized_csv.index)  #  
df_normalized_csv.reset_index(inplace=True)
df_normalized_csv.rename(columns={"": ""}, inplace=True)  # PowerBI   

df_normalized_csv.to_csv(os.path.join(powerbi_data_DIR, "PowerBI_antihistamine_trend.csv"), encoding="cp949", index=False)

#  
plt.figure(figsize=(14, 6))
for name in antihistamines.values():
    plt.plot(df_normalized.index, df_normalized[name], marker="o", label=name)

plt.title("/     (Z-score )")
plt.xlabel("/")
plt.ylabel("  ")
plt.legend(title="", bbox_to_anchor=(1.05, 1), loc="upper left")
plt.grid(True, linestyle="--", alpha=0.7)

# x   /    
plt.xticks(ticks=range(len(df_normalized.index)), labels=df_normalized.index, rotation=45, ha="right")

plt.show()
